25|$|During World War II, on 27 August 1944, {{the infant}} school {{was hit by}} a V-1 <b>flying</b> <b>bomb</b> and demolished. This {{occurred}} early on a Sunday morning, and the school was empty. The only casualty was the Rector, who was in his garden not far away and was injured. Another <b>flying</b> <b>bomb</b> hit the gasholder on the Common, destroying both the structure and a nearby cottage, whose occupant was killed.|$|E
