25|$|Half {{a million}} Morrison shelters had been {{distributed}} {{by the end of}} 1941, with a further 100,000 being added in 1943 to prepare the population for the expected German V-1 <b>flying</b> <b>bomb</b> (doodlebug) attacks.|$|E
25|$|By late 1943, Maj. Gen. Henry H. Arnold {{directed}} Brig. Gen. Grandison Gardner's electronic {{engineers at}} Eglin Field, Florida, to outfit war-weary bombers with automatic pilots {{so that they}} could be remotely controlled. This was the preliminary work for the Operation Aphrodite <b>flying</b> <b>bomb</b> drone missions in Europe in 1944.|$|E
